    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-3126438">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-3126438">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,3126438)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-3126438">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227299" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1499427568 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Jul 2017 11:39</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3126438">
									

<p>The suggestions about title and summary of the forum post are valuable. :) In my experience, soliciting for feedback results in one, maybe two responses, followed by silence and summary downvotes when I post. It's almost always worse in chat, where solicitations have no permanency and draft trades almost always leave me swapping feedback with someone who's just starting.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It points out objective errors, such as typos and formatting issues.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I would argue with this, insofar as <em>only</em> pointing out typos and formatting errors is not useful feedback. An experienced critic should know those things are window-dressing, and shouldn't be addressed until the underlying substance of the draft is cleaned up, save for cases where readability is affected.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>It is very insistent that you should not write about this subject matter, or that you are handling the subject matter poorly.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>So saying &quot;I don't like X, you really, really shouldn't write about X&quot; is good critique? I feel like this needs to be reworded.</p>

							</div>

								
					
